# Accessibility

## Semantic HTML

Use `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<section>`, `<article>` appropriately. Public pages already use `Layout` with `<main>` — do not nest duplicate `<main>` tags.

## Icon-only buttons

Every icon button needs an accessible name:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<button aria-label={t("common.close")}><X /></button>

// ❌ BAD
<button><X /></button>
```

## Images

Decorative images: `alt=""`. Meaningful images: descriptive `alt` text (hero name, item name).

## Dialogs & selects

Use Radix primitives from `src/components/ui/core.tsx` (`Dialog`, `Select`) — they provide focus trap, Escape to close, and keyboard navigation. Do not build custom modals with bare `div` overlays.

## Focus visibility

Interactive elements must have visible focus states. Do not remove `outline` without replacing with a custom `focus-visible:` ring using brand tokens.

## Motion

Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` when adding new animations (motion/react). Avoid autoplaying motion that cannot be paused.
